INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Human Resources Administration and the Department of Youth and Community Development to publish on the agencies’ websites information relating to the process for youth and young adults aged sixteen through twenty applying for or receiving public assistance.
EventItemMatterName: HRA and the Dept of Youth & Community Development to publish on the agencies’ websites information relating to the process for youth & young adults aged 16 through 20 applying for or receiving public assistance.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reporting requirements for the department of citywide administrative services on the status of city-owned real property.
EventItemMatterName: Reporting requirements for DCAS on the status of city-owned real property.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States House of Representatives and the United States Senate to pass and the President to sign H.R. 1390 entitled “The Bus Uniform Standards and Enhanced Safety Act of 2011,” which would seek to strengthen the regulation, monitoring and oversight of the motor carrier industry.
EventItemMatterName: The Bus Uniform Standards and Enhanced Safety Act of 2011 (H.R. 1390)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress and the President of the United States to increase funding for research on stroke prevention and treatment.
EventItemMatterName: Increase funding for research on stroke prevention and treatment.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon New York State to amend the Social Services Law in order to allow a parent or other relative of a child up to age one exemption from participation in welfare to work activities.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the Social Services Law in order to allow a parent or other relative of a child up to age one exemption from participation in welfare to work activities.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Human Resources Administration to clarify the process for serving youth and young adults aged 16 through twenty-four receiving public assistance as head of household.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring HRA to clarify the process for serving youth & young adults aged 16 through 24 receiving public assistance as head of household.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Bloomberg Administration to discontinue the use and development of Worker Connect, a shared database that gives workers across health and human services agencies access to personal client information.
EventItemMatterName: Bloomberg Administration to discontinue the use and development of Worker Connect.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to permitting the appeal of decisions by the board of standards and appeals to the city council.
EventItemMatterName: Permitting the appeal of decisions by the board of standards and appeals to the city council.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to expiration of variances granted by the board of standards and appeals.
EventItemMatterName: Expiration of variances granted by the board of standards and appeals.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring signs at shared bicycle and pedestrian paths.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring signs at shared bicycle and pedestrian paths.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the registration of owners of vacant property.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the registration of owners of vacant property.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Information Technology and Telecommunications to work with the New York City Police and Fire Departments as well as wireless carriers to develop a plan that would allow New York City residents to contact 911 and 311 through text messages.
EventItemMatterName: Develop a plan that would allow New York City residents to contact 911 and 311 through text messages.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating an interagency task force on electric assisted bicycle safety.
EventItemMatterName: Creating an interagency task force on electric assisted bicycle safety.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to animal shelters in the city of New York, to repeal section 17-801 in relation thereto, and to repeal and re-enact section 17-809.
EventItemMatterName: Animal shelters in NYC, to repeal section 17-801 in relation thereto, and to repeal and re-enact section 17-809.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to persons not to be detained.
EventItemMatterName: Persons not to be detained.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting the Governor’s proposal to amend the Penal Law to make possession of a small quantity of marihuana in public view a violation, applauding the Speaker of the Assembly for his support of the proposal, and calling upon the New York Senate to pass legislation enacting the same.
EventItemMatterName: Make possession of a small quantity of marihuana in public view a violation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to collecting and reporting data related to access of individuals aged sixteen through twenty-four to public assistance as head of household.
EventItemMatterName: Collecting and reporting data related to access of individuals aged 16 through 24 to public assistance as head of household.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.
EventItemMatterName: Approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reporting requirements for housing subsidies provided by the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Reporting requirements for housing subsidies provided by the city of New York.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the waiver of public employee organizations’ rights when submitting grievances to arbitration under the New York city collective bargaining law.
EventItemMatterName: Waiver of public employee organizations’ rights when submitting grievances to arbitration under the NYC collective bargaining law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing notice regarding permits for movie-making, telecasting and photography in public places.
EventItemMatterName: Providing notice regarding permits for movie-making, telecasting and photography in public places.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Department of Homeless Services to report on a monthly basis the location of all of their facilities.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the Department of Homeless Services to report on a monthly basis the location of all of their facilities.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Community Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Federal Reserve Bank to rescind its proposed rule requiring borrowers to pay off the remaining principal on a mortgage before the lender is forced to cancel its security interest in the home.
EventItemMatterName: Federal Reserve Bank to rescind its proposed rule requiring borrowers to pay off the remaining principal on a mortgage before the lender is forced to cancel its security interest in the home.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Community Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature and the Governor to enact legislation that would prohibit lenders from concealing mortgage assignments through the use of the Mortgage Electronic Registration System, Inc., known as MERS.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibit lenders from concealing mortgage assignments through the use of the Mortgage Electronic Registration System, Inc., known as MERS.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Community Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature and the Governor to enact legislation that would require the foreclosing party in a mortgage foreclosure action to produce the pooling and service agreement at the commencement of a mortgage foreclosure action.
EventItemMatterName: Require the foreclosing party in a mortgage foreclosure action to produce the pooling and service agreement at the commencement of a mortgage foreclosure action.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to increasing the fines for commercial vehicles that park on residential streets.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing the fines for commercial vehicles that park on residential streets

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to allowing violations to be issued based on vehicle identification numbers.
EventItemMatterName: Allowing violations to be issued based on vehicle identification numbers.
